Name: spinal cord lipoma
Definition: A central nervous system lipoma that is characterized by abnormal fat accumulation in and around the spinal cord.

Name: cerebral hemisphere lipoma
Definition: A heart lipoma that is located_in the epicardium and derives_from fat cells.

Name: obsolete intracranial lipoma
Definition: A heart lipoma that is located_in the epicardium and derives_from fat cells.
